hwVrrpExt.name: hwVrrpExt

revisions.description: Fix the errors checked by a tool.

hwVrrpExt.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwVrrpExt.description: It supplies for VRRP tracking function.

hwVrrpExtFreeArpInterval.name: hwVrrpExtFreeArpInterval
hwVrrpExtFreeArpInterval.description: This object indicates the interval at which gratuitous ARP packets are sent. Zero means the gratuitous-arp sending function is disable.

hwVrrpExtVIPPingCtr.name: hwVrrpExtVIPPingCtr
hwVrrpExtVIPPingCtr.description: A switch decides whether the system responds to a request message or not, which is sent to virtual ip address. The default value is enable.

hwVrrpExtSsTimer.name: hwVrrpExtSsTimer
hwVrrpExtSsTimer.description: A switch decides whether the system enable VRRP SS function and set the size of VRRP SS timer or not, which decide the VRRP packet advertisement interval during slave switchover. The default value is 100s. But for the VRRP v3 version,this time value is truncated to 40950 milliseconds which is the maximum value according to the RFC 5798.

hwVrrpExtLearnAdvIntervalFlag.name: hwVrrpExtLearnAdvIntervalFlag
hwVrrpExtLearnAdvIntervalFlag.description: A switch decides whether the system learn VRRP packet advertisement interval or not, which is sended from the master router in one virtual router standby. The default value is enable.

hwVrrpExtProtocolVersion.name: hwVrrpExtProtocolVersion
hwVrrpExtProtocolVersion.description: Current protocol verison for VRRP on the specified device.The default value is v2(2) , and the other value for this element is v3(3).

hwVrrpExtSendV3AdverPktMode.name: hwVrrpExtSendV3AdverPktMode
hwVrrpExtSendV3AdverPktMode.description: This value specifies the mode of sending advertisement packet for VRRP v3.It has three configurable value: VRRP_PROTO_V3_SEND_V2_ONLY(1), VRRP_PROTO_V3_SEND_V3_ONLY(2) and VRRP_PROTO_V3_SEND_V3V2_BOTH(3).

hwVrrpExtStateChangeReasonString.name: hwVrrpExtStateChangeReasonString
hwVrrpExtStateChangeReasonString.description: Reasons of VRRP state transition. Used by hwVrrpExtTrapNonMaster, hwVrrpExtTrapMasterDown trap and vrrpTrapNewMaster trap.

hwVrrpTrackInterTable.name: hwVrrpTrackInterTable
hwVrrpTrackInterTable.description: The VRRP tracking interface table, it can accomodate eight rows at most.

hwVrrpTrackInterEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackInterEntry
hwVrrpTrackInterEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP tracking interface table.

hwVrrpTrackInterVRID.name: hwVrrpTrackInterVRID
hwVrrpTrackInterVRID.description: The index of the VRRP tracking interface table, it identifies the standby's ID.

hwVrrpTrackInterStandByIfnet.name: hwVrrpTrackInterStandByIfnet
hwVrrpTrackInterStandByIfnet.description: The index of the VRRP tracking interface table, it identifies the standby's interface index.

hwVrrpTrackInterIfnet.name: hwVrrpTrackInterIfnet
hwVrrpTrackInterIfnet.description: The index of the VRRP tracking interface table, it identifies the tracked interface index.

hwVrrpTrackInterPriReduce.name: hwVrrpTrackInterPriReduce
hwVrrpTrackInterPriReduce.description: If the tracked interface is down, priority of standby will reduce this value. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.

hwVrrpTrackInterPriIncrease.name: hwVrrpTrackInterPriIncrease
hwVrrpTrackInterPriIncrease.description: If the tracked interface is down, this value will be added to the priority of standby. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.

hwVrrpTrackBfdTable.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdTable
hwVrrpTrackBfdTable.description: The VRRP tracking BFD table, it can append eight rows at most.

hwVrrpTrackBfdEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdEntry
hwVrrpTrackBfdEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP tracking BFD table.

hwVrrpTrackBfdId.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdId
hwVrrpTrackBfdId.description: The index of the table, it only identifies BFD link.

hwVrrpTrackBfdPriReduce.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdPriReduce
hwVrrpTrackBfdPriReduce.description: If the tracked BFD is down, the priority of standby will reduce this value. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.

hwVrrpTrackBfdPriIncrease.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdPriIncrease
hwVrrpTrackBfdPriIncrease.description: If the tracked BFD is down, this value will be added to the priority of standby. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.

hwVrrpTrackBfdType.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdType
hwVrrpTrackBfdType.description: The bfd type that vrrp tracks,including Normal, Link, Peer. The attribute cannot be modified after created.

hwVrrpTrackBfdName.name: hwVrrpTrackBfdName
hwVrrpTrackBfdName.description: The bfd name that vrrp tracks. The attribute cannot be modified after created.

hwAdminVrrpCfgIgnoreIfDownMode.name: hwAdminVrrpCfgIgnoreIfDownMode
hwAdminVrrpCfgIgnoreIfDownMode.description: The mode of ignore interface down.

hwVrrpStatResetFlag.name: hwVrrpStatResetFlag
hwVrrpStatResetFlag.description: A reset signal of vrrp statistics.

hwAdminVrrpTrackIfTable.name: hwAdminVrrpTrackIfTable
hwAdminVrrpTrackIfTable.description: The interface bound to VRRP table.

hwAdminVrrpTrackIfEntry.name: hwAdminVrrpTrackIfEntry
hwAdminVrrpTrackIfEntry.description: Entries of the interface bound to VRRP table.

hwAdminVrrpIfIndex.name: hwAdminVrrpIfIndex
hwAdminVrrpIfIndex.description: The administrator VRRP's configure interface index.

hwAdminVrrpTrackIfRowStatus.name: hwAdminVrrpTrackIfRowStatus
hwAdminVrrpTrackIfRowStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

hwVrrpTrackEfmEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmEntry
hwVrrpTrackEfmEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP tracking EFM table.

hwVrrpTrackEfmIfIndex.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmIfIndex
hwVrrpTrackEfmIfIndex.description: The index of the table, it identifies vrrp's interface index.

hwVrrpTrackEfmIfName.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmIfName
hwVrrpTrackEfmIfName.description: A textual string containing information about the interface of vrrp.

hwVrrpTrackEfmVRID.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmVRID
hwVrrpTrackEfmVRID.description: The index of the table, it identifies vrrp's vrid.

hwVrrpTrackEfmIndex.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmIndex
hwVrrpTrackEfmIndex.description: The index of the table, it identifies EFM's interface index.

hwVrrpTrackEfmName.name: hwVrrpTrackEfmName
hwVrrpTrackEfmName.description: A textual string containing information about the interface of efm.

hwVrrpTriggerRouteEntry.name: hwVrrpTriggerRouteEntry
hwVrrpTriggerRouteEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP trigger route table.

hwVrrpTriggerRouteIfIndex.name: hwVrrpTriggerRouteIfIndex
hwVrrpTriggerRouteIfIndex.description: The index of the table, it identifies vrrp's interface index.

hwVrrpTriggerRouteMode.name: hwVrrpTriggerRouteMode
hwVrrpTriggerRouteMode.description: A switch decides whether the system responds to a request message or not, which is sent to virtual ip address.

hwVrrpCfgEntry.name: hwVrrpCfgEntry
hwVrrpCfgEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP configure route table.

hwVrrpCfgIfIndex.name: hwVrrpCfgIfIndex
hwVrrpCfgIfIndex.description: The index of the table, it identifies vrrp's interface index.

hwVrrpCfgLinkBfdDownNumber.name: hwVrrpCfgLinkBfdDownNumber
hwVrrpCfgLinkBfdDownNumber.description: The state of link BFD will really down when reach the configured down number. Enter '0' to delete this configuration.

hwVrrpCfgMsecAdvInterval.name: hwVrrpCfgMsecAdvInterval
hwVrrpCfgMsecAdvInterval.description: The value of VRRP advertise interval in milliseconds, when the interval is less than 1 second, otherwise it should be set or got in VRRP-MIB. when the advertise interval is equal to or larger than 1 second, this value will be 0.

hwVrrpCfgFastResumeFlag.name: hwVrrpCfgFastResumeFlag
hwVrrpCfgFastResumeFlag.description: A switch indicates whether the VRRP fast-resume function is enabled.

hwVrrpStatExtEntry.name: hwVrrpStatExtEntry
hwVrrpStatExtEntry.description: An entry in The VRRP statistics extend table.

hwVrrpStatExtIfIndex.name: hwVrrpStatExtIfIndex
hwVrrpStatExtIfIndex.description: The index of the table, it identifies vrrp's interface index.

hwVrrpStatExtBecomeBackup.name: hwVrrpStatExtBecomeBackup
hwVrrpStatExtBecomeBackup.description: The total number of times that this virtual router's state has transitioned to BACKUP.

hwVrrpStatExtBecomeInit.name: hwVrrpStatExtBecomeInit
hwVrrpStatExtBecomeInit.description: The total number of times that this virtual router's state has transitioned to INITIALIZE.

hwVrrpStatExtLastChangeTime.name: hwVrrpStatExtLastChangeTime
hwVrrpStatExtLastChangeTime.description: The last change time of vrrp.

hwVrrpExtTrapMasterDown.name: hwVrrpExtTrapMasterDown
hwVrrpExtTrapMasterDown.description: The MasterDown trap indicates that the state of vrrp has transitioned from 'Master' to other state. The other state can be noactive(0), initialize(1) and backup(2).

hwVrrpExtTrapNonMaster.name: hwVrrpExtTrapNonMaster
hwVrrpExtTrapNonMaster.description: The NonMaster trap indicates that the state of vrrp has transitioned between Backup and Initialize state.

hwvrrpExtCompliance.name: hwvrrpExtCompliance
hwvrrpExtCompliance.description: The core compliance statement for all VRRP implementations.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceTable.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceTable
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceTable.description: This object indicates the VRRP tracking Ipsec-instance table, which can accommodate a maximum of eight rows.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceEntry
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceEntry.description: This object indicates an entry in the VRRP tracking Ipsec-instance table.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceVRID.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceVRID
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceVRID.description: The value of this object identifies the ID of a backup device in the VRRP tracking Ipsec-instance table.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceStandByIfnet.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceStandByIfnet
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceStandByIfnet.description: The value of this object identifies the interface index of a backup device in the VRRP tracking Ipsec-instance table.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceID.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceID
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceID.description: The value of this object identifies the ID of a tracked Ipsec-instance in the VRRP tracking Ipsec-instance table.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstancePriReduce.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstancePriReduce
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstancePriReduce.description: If the tracked Ipsec-instance is Down, priorities of backup devices decrease by the specified value. The value 0 indicates that the attribute is not configured. The minimum value is 1.

hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceOperRowStatus.name: hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceOperRowStatus
hwVrrpTrackIpsecInstanceOperRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status variable.

hwVrrpTrackNQAEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAEntry
hwVrrpTrackNQAEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP tracking NQA table.

hwVrrpTrackNQAVRID.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAVRID
hwVrrpTrackNQAVRID.description: The value of this object identifies the ID of a backup device in the VRRP tracking NQA table.

hwVrrpTrackNQAStandbyIfIndex.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAStandbyIfIndex
hwVrrpTrackNQAStandbyIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface index of a backup device in the VRRP tracking NQA table.

hwVrrpTrackNQAAdminName.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAAdminName
hwVrrpTrackNQAAdminName.description: The NQA administer name that vrrp tracks. The attribute cannot be modified after created.

hwVrrpTrackNQATestName.name: hwVrrpTrackNQATestName
hwVrrpTrackNQATestName.description: The NQA test name that vrrp tracks. The attribute cannot be modified after created.

hwVrrpTrackNQAPriReduce.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAPriReduce
hwVrrpTrackNQAPriReduce.description: If the tracked NQA is down, the priority of standby will reduce this value. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.

hwVrrpTrackNQAOperRowStatus.name: hwVrrpTrackNQAOperRowStatus
hwVrrpTrackNQAOperRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status variable.

hwVrrpTrackRouteEntry.name: hwVrrpTrackRouteEntry
hwVrrpTrackRouteEntry.description: An entry in the VRRP tracking Route table.

hwVrrpTrackRouteVRID.name: hwVrrpTrackRouteVRID
hwVrrpTrackRouteVRID.description: The index of the VRRP tracking Route table, it identifies the standby's ID.

hwVrrpTrackRouteIndex.name: hwVrrpTrackRouteIndex
hwVrrpTrackRouteIndex.description: The index of the VRRP tracking Route table, it identifies the standby's interface index.

hwVrrpTrackRoutePrefix.name: hwVrrpTrackRoutePrefix
hwVrrpTrackRoutePrefix.description: The index of the VRRP tracking Route table, it identifies the tracked ip address.

hwVrrpTrackRouteMask.name: hwVrrpTrackRouteMask
hwVrrpTrackRouteMask.description: The index of the VRRP tracking Route table, it identifies the tracked ip address's mask.

hwVrrpTrackRouteVrf.name: hwVrrpTrackRouteVrf
hwVrrpTrackRouteVrf.description: The index of the VRRP tracking Route table, it identifies the tracked VPN instance name

hwVrrpTrackRoutePriReduce.name: hwVrrpTrackRoutePriReduce
hwVrrpTrackRoutePriReduce.description: If the tracked route is unreachable, the priority of standby will reduce this value. '0' specifies this attribute hasn't been configured. The minimum availability value is '1'.
